# Changelog — RavLight Core

Format: [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/)
Versioning: [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html)

---

## [2.12.0] — 2026-04-29

### Added
- **Multi-universe DMX pool** — `dmx_manager` now maintains a pool of up to 32 universes (`DMX_MAX_UNIVERSES`); fixtures call `registerDmxUniverse()` at startup and read live data via `getUniverseData()`; backward compatible (single-universe fixtures like Veyron unchanged)
- **Native ArtNet/sACN** — `hideakitai/ArtNet` and `ESPAsyncE131` libraries replaced with lwIP raw UDP sockets; ArtNet on port 6454 (`INADDR_ANY`) receives from all interfaces simultaneously (ETH, WiFi STA, AP); sACN on port 5568 joins a multicast group per universe — no consecutive-universe limitation
- **ArtPoll reply** — device responds to ArtPoll requests with a minimal ArtPollReply (short name, long name, universe, MAC) for automatic discovery by Resolume, GrandMA, etc.
- **ArtNet auto-reinit** — when Ethernet or WiFi connects (or AP starts), DMX inputs automatically reinitialise without device restart
- **Elyon multi-universe renderer** — each of the 8 outputs can span multiple universes; pixel-to-channel mapping uses flat channel index math across universe boundaries

### Fixed
- **Config save crash** (guru meditation) — NVS buffer was stack-allocated inside an AsyncWebServer callback (limited stack); moved to heap (`malloc`/`free`)
- **ArtNet crash with Ethernet disconnected** — `artnet.begin()` (EthernetUDP) fails silently when Ethernet is not up, leaving an internal null socket; `artnet.parse()` then dereferenced it; guarded with `ETH.linkUp()` check and `artnetReady` flag
- **SoftAP name** — access point was named with the MAC address placeholder; now uses `PROJECT_NAME-ID_fixture` format (e.g. `RavLight-A1B2`)

### Removed
- `hideakitai/ArtNet`, `ESPAsyncE131`, `arduino-libraries/Ethernet` library dependencies — replaced by native lwIP socket implementation

---

## [2.11.0] — 2026-04-28

### Added
- **QuinLED Dig-Octa Brainboard-32-8L support** — new board file `boards/quinled_octa.h`; 8 LED output GPIOs (0,1,2,3,4,5,12,13), LAN8720A Ethernet (ETH_CLOCK_GPIO17_OUT, no power pin)
- **Elyon fixture** — 8-output LED controller; each output independently configured with pixel count and DMX start address; personality selects 1/2/4/8 active outputs; all driven via IDF 4.4 RMT (`RMT_CHANNEL_0..7`, `mem_blocks=1`)
- **`env:quinled_octa_elyon`** — QuinLED Dig-Octa + Elyon build environment in `platformio.ini`
- **`RAVLIGHT_HAS_STATUS_LED`** capability flag — status LED `pinMode`/`digitalWrite` in `dmx_manager` now guarded; boards without a status LED compile cleanly

---

## [2.10.0] — 2026-04-28

### Added
- **Native LED drivers** — FastLED and NeoPixelBus removed; WS2811 strip now driven via ESP-IDF 4.4 RMT (`led_output_t`, `src/core/led_output.cpp`); P9813 accent pixels via GPIO bit-bang (`p9813_t`, `src/core/p9813.cpp`)
- **`led_output_t`** — generic RMT LED strip driver abstraction; one instance per channel; ready for Elyon (8 independent RMT channels)
- **`p9813_t`** — P9813 bit-bang driver; start/end frame protocol; no SPI library dependency

### Fixed
- **WS2811 white-glitch at low brightness** — the strip uses 800 kHz WS2812B-compatible protocol; the original 400 kHz T0H (500 ns) exceeded the strip's ~600 ns threshold and was read as `1` by every zero bit; corrected to T0H = 400 ns (clk_div=4, 50 ns/tick)

---

## [2.9.0] — 2026-04-27

### Added
- **LittleFS** replaces SPIFFS — better wear leveling and power-cut resilience; partition format migrates automatically on first boot
- **Config in NVS** — device configuration now stored in NVS blob (namespace `ravlight`), completely separate from the filesystem; uploading new web assets via `uploadfs` no longer wipes WiFi credentials and settings
- **DMX Recorder — complete** — records any DMX source (ArtNet, sACN, wired) into 4 slots at 40 fps for 10 s each; slot selection and active slot saved in config and survive restart
- **Auto Scene playback** — selecting *Auto Scene* as DMX source loops the chosen slot continuously without any separate play button; switching to another source stops playback immediately; changing slot mid-playback takes effect on the next Save without switching source
- **Recording feedback** — Web UI polls the device and shows a *Recording complete* notification when the 10 s capture finishes
- **IDF API migration (Fase 1)** — `runtime`, `config`, and `dmx_recorder` modules now use native ESP-IDF calls: `ESP_LOG*`, `esp_timer_get_time`, `esp_wifi_get_mac`, `gpio_set_direction`/`gpio_get_level`, `esp_restart`
- **`dmxBuffer` mutex** — protects concurrent access to the DMX buffer from network callbacks and the recorder task

### Changed
- `runtimeNVS` module renamed to `runtime`; NVS flash initialisation moved to `config` (primary NVS owner); runtime data in separate namespace `runtime`
- Config upload/download handlers rewritten to use in-memory struct serialisation instead of reading `/config.json` from filesystem
- DMX source dropdown order: ArtNet → sACN → DMX Wired → Auto Scene

### Fixed
- Accumulated runtime hours preserved across firmware upgrades via one-shot NVS namespace migration (`storage` → `runtime`)
- LED output was frozen during scene playback — the renderer was incorrectly gated by the same flag used to block live DMX input

---

## [2.8.0] — 2026-04-27

### Added
- **DMX patch list system** — semantic channel typing for fixture personalities: each output channel carries its type, section, default value, and count; enables fixture-agnostic rendering logic
- **Fixture webserver architecture** — Veyron-specific web routes, HTML injection and save parameter handling moved into `src/fixtures/veyron/`; shared web server code is now fixture-independent
- **Restart overlay** — when saving WiFi or network settings, a countdown overlay appears immediately and redirects automatically to the device mDNS address after 10 seconds
- **Axon and Elyon fixture headers** — skeleton personality tables for the ArtNet-to-RS485 bridge (Axon) and 8-output LED controller (Elyon)

### Changed
- Dimming Curve setting moved from general Settings into the Veyron Fixture accordion
- Scene Recorder moved from the Veyron Fixture accordion into the DMX accordion (it is a DMX module, not fixture-specific)

### Fixed
- Saving DMX address or personality no longer restarts the device — restart now only triggers when WiFi, IP or fixture ID actually change
- Device restart after network save now completes reliably (was dropping the HTTP response before transmitting it)

---

## [2.7.0] — 2026-04-24

### Added
- **Board file pattern** (`boards/`) — port RavLight to any ESP32 board by adding a single header file; no core code changes needed
- **`RAVLIGHT_MODULE_ETHERNET`** — Ethernet support is now an explicit compile-time flag; WiFi-only boards compile cleanly without it
- **Config JSON v2** — settings file restructured in named sections (`network`, `dmx`, `fixture`); auto-migrates from v1 on first boot
- **Board name in Web UI header** — shows which board is running at a glance

### Changed
- PlatformIO environment renamed `veyron` → `xdmx_v2_veyron` (board + fixture naming)
- DMX Recorder is in progress — record/playback not yet complete

### Fixed
- Dimming curve selection was off-by-one: Linear/Square/Inverse Square/S-Curve now map correctly to the Web UI dropdowns

---

## [2.6.0] — 2025-07-17

### Added
- Configuration file export (`/download_config`) and import (`/upload_config`) from the Web UI Settings panel

---

## [2.5.0] — 2025-06-14

### Added
- UDP discovery (port 4210/4211) — fixture responds to `R_DISCOVER` broadcast for future app integration
- ESP-NOW discovery — works without network infrastructure
- UDP command receiver (port 4212): RESET, APMODE, CONNECT, HIGHLIGHT

---

## [2.4.0] — 2025-04-05

### Added
- 5 DMX personalities for the Veyron 40-pixel fixture:

  | # | Name | Channels |
  |---|------|----------|
  | 1 | Full Spectrum Control | 128 |
  | 2 | Pure Pixel – No Strobe | 126 |
  | 3 | Simplified Master | 8 |
  | 4 | Mirror Mode | ~68 |
  | 5 | Grouped Pixel Control | ~68 |

---

## [2.0.0] — 2025-03-20

### Added
- Veyron LED Bar spec locked: ArtNet + sACN + physical DMX RS-485, 40+6 pixels, 4 dimming curves, SoftAP first-setup, Web UI on Ethernet and WiFi

---

## [1.3.0] — 2025-03-05

### Added
- Web UI collapsible accordion sections

### Fixed
- SPIFFS OTA was overwriting `config.json` — fixed via partition separation

---

## [1.1.0] — 2025-01-12

### Added
- DMX Scene Recorder v1: 4 slots, 40 FPS, 10 s per slot (playback integration in progress)

---

## [1.0.0] — 2024-12-22

### Added
- Hardware config reset: hold button 10 s → wipes config and restores defaults
- DMX timeout: LEDs blackout if no frame within 50 ms
- Web UI reset button

---

## [0.0.1] — 2024-09-25

### Added
- First complete firmware build: ArtNet + sACN + physical DMX, embedded Web UI, DHCP/static IP, universe and start address configuration

